

// BUBBLE SORT-  0(n^2)

WHAT WE DO IS SWAP THE ADJACENT ELEMENT IF THE Ith element is Bigger than (Ith + 1) element.
in this way we swap the biggest element to the last always like a bubble.
The way bubble goes at the top.

we do this n-1 time because at last 2 elemets after swaping 1 iteration is saved.

and at every i we see the adjacent elements.

for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++)
{
    int flag = 0;
    for(int j=0;j<n-1-i;j++)
    {
        if(a[j] > a[j+1])
        {
            swap(a[j],a[j+1]);
            flag = 1;
        }
        
       
    }
    
        if(flag==0) break;
}

